OL,3,C'It's been 42 years': Infected blood
OL,4,Cvictim still waiting for compensation
OL,6,FNeil Walker, a victim of the scandal
OL,7,Fand his wife Tina Walker told ITV News
OL,8,FCentral that "as the years go on more
OL,9,Fpeople from the community are dying"
OL,11,FVictims of the infected blood scandal
OL,12,Fliving in the Midlands say they are
OL,13,Ffrustrated that the government has
OL,14,Fstill not paid them the compensation
OL,15,Fthat they were promised.
OL,17,FNeil Walker from Derby is one of the
OL,18,F30,000 people in the UK who were given
OL,19,Ftreatments infected with HIV and
OL,20,Fhepatitis C during the 1970s and 80s.
