OL,3,C'It's been 42 years': Infected blood
OL,4,Cvictim still waiting for compensation
OL,6,FIn May 2024 the government published
OL,7,Ftheir final report into the scandal
OL,8,Fand acknowledged responsibility for
OL,9,Fthe harms caused.
OL,11,FThe government set aside #11.8bn to
OL,12,Fcompensate victims of the infected
OL,13,Fblood scandal, after a public inquiry
OL,14,Ffound the authorities had covered up
OL,15,Fthe scale of the problem.
